quran[19]{c,v,t}:
  15,52,"When they visited him, they greeted him with Salam (peace on you). He said, "We are scared of you.""
  15,53,"They said, 'Do not be scared. We give you good news of a boy who will be knowledgeable.""
  15,54,"He said, "Do you give me the good news while old age has befallen me? So what is the good news you are giving to me?""
  15,55,"They said, "We have given to you the good news of a fact. So do not be among those who lose hope.""
  15,56,"He said, "Who would lose hope in the mercy of his Lord except those who have lost the straight path?""
  15,57,"He said, 'Then, what is your mission, 0 messengers?'"
  15,58,"They said, "We have been sent to a sinful people,"
  15,59,"except the family of Lut - all of whom we shall save,"
  15,60,"but his wife. We have ordained that she is to be among those who will remain behind.""
  15,61,"So when the messengers came to the family of Lut"
  15,62,"he said, "you are an unusual people.""
  15,63,"They said, 'No, but we have brought to you what they have been doubting in."
  15,64,"And we have come to you with a definite matter and surely we are truthful."
  15,65,"So, carry your family after a part of the night (has passed) and follow them at the rear and no one from you should look back and keep going to where you are commanded.""
  15,66,"And We revealed to him the fact that they are to be annihilated to the last man when they see the morning."
  15,67,"And the people of the city came rejoicing."
  15,68,"He (Lilt) said, 'They are my guests; so do not put me to shame"
  15,69,"and fear Allah and do not disgrace me.""
  15,70,"They said, 'Had we not forbidden you from (being the guardian of) the whole world?""